A '''government contractor''' is a company ([[Private company|privately owned]] or [[Public company|publicly traded]] but not a [[state-owned enterprise]]){{spaced ndash}}either [[for profit]] or [[non-profit]]{{spaced ndash}}that produces goods or services under contract for the [[government]].  Some communities are largely sustained by government contracting activity; for instance, much of the economy of [[Northern Virginia]] consists of government contractors employed directly or indirectly by the [[federal government]] of the [[United States]].

==United Kingdom==
Section 12(2) and (3) of the Official Secrets Act 1989 define the expression 
"Government Contractor" for the purposes of that Act.

