'''Yuen Mo''' ({{zh|c=袁武|p=Yuán Wǔ}}) <small>[[Hong Kong honours system|GBS]] [[Justice of the Peace|JP]]</small> (born November 1941) is a business leader in [[Hong Kong]].

He joined [[China Merchants]], a shipping company, in 1964, and served in various positions<ref>{{cite news|last=Chen|first=Bonnie|title=NPC election to see no more than 60 candidates |url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?pp_cat=11&art_id=60040&sid=17105871&con_type=1|accessdate=2 January 2011|newspaper=[[The Standard (Hong Kong)|The Standard]]|date=15 January 2008}}</ref> such as Deputy General Manager of Hong Kong Ming Wah Shipping Co. Ltd., Deputy General Manager of China Merchants Steam Navigation Co. Ltd.

Yuen was also a member of the 8th [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]], Member of the Preparatory Committee of the [[Hong Kong|Hong Kong Special Administrative Region]], a member of the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Provisional Legislative Council]] of Hong Kong, and member of the first [[Election Committee]] to elect 10 of the 60 seats of the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council]] in 1998.

At present, he is concurrently serving as Chairman of China Merchants Industry Holdings and Vice Chairman of China Merchants Zhangzhou Economic Development Zone. Yuen is Deputy to the Ninth [[National People's Congress]] and conveor of deputies from Hong Kong, a [[Justice of the Peace]], a Member of the [[Election Committee]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Four Hong Kong delegates named to Chinese NPC presidium|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=NewsLibrary&p_multi=BBAB&d_place=BBAB&p_theme=newslibrary2&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0F99E86575199F55&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|accessdate=2 January 2011|newspaper=[[BBC]], [[Radio Television Hong Kong]] Radio 3|date=4 March 2003}}</ref> Member of Citizens Advisory Committee on Community Relations of [[Independent Commission Against Corruption (Hong Kong)|ICAC]], and Executive Director of the Hong Kong Chinese Enterprises Association.

Yuen Mo traces his ancestry to the [[Yuan (surname)|Yuan]] clan of [[Dongguan]] and has ties with the Hong Kong Association of Yuan Clansmen ({{zh|s=香港袁氏宗亲会|t=香港袁氏宗親會|p=Xiāng Gǎng Yuán shì zōngqīn huì}}). In 2001, he led a group of Hong Kong and [[Shenzhen]]-based Yuan clan businessmen to Ru'nan, where they attended local cultural events and discussed with provincial officials the possibility of investing in local industry.

